<br>
Can't make it clearer than that.  Trains happen.  CB is a train zone.  I was KS'd by them and killed early by someone insensitive enough to run around the zone and through my fight near the water instead of zoning.  I was out of the way but the Paladin decided to maybe see if one of his adds may stick to me.  Can't think of another reason other than he got lost but he ran by the tunnel twice before ( I was facing it).  <br>
<br>
The game is realistic because humans play it.  There are all types.  I move on and am not that upset.  I just could not believe the actions of those elfs in corner nor the stupidity of the HIE Paly.<br>
<br>
As for helping others, I try to buff, heal or taunt/bash mobs without attacking.  Only if they are trying to zone may I attack.  <br>
<br>
Like I said, I have played the game a long time like most of you.  This was not the first time I have seen stuff like this nor the last.  But I will smile the day those 7 need my help.<br>
<br>
